Executive Profile
Raymond P. Silcock  Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President, CTI Foods Holding Co., LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 13 different industries.See Board Relationships67--
Background

		Mr. Raymond P. Silcock, also known as Ray serves as the Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President at CTI Foods Holding Co., LLC since June 6, 2016. Currently, he also serves as an Advisory Partner at Alliance Consumer Growth, where he focuses on Food & Beverage industry. Prior to firm, he served as the Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President at Diamond Foods, Inc. from June 11, 2013 to February 29, 2016. Prior to that, Mr. Silcock served as the ... Chief Financial Officer at The Great Atlantic & Pacific Tea Company, Inc. since March 13, 2012, where he joined the firm in December 2011 as the Head of Finance. Prior to that, he served as an Executive-in-Residence at Palm Ventures LLC. Prior to that, Mr. Silcock served as the Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President at KB Home from September 2009 to December 14, 2009. Prior to that, he served as the Chief Financial Officer and Senior Vice President at UST LLC from August 6, 2007 to January 2009. Prior to that, Mr. Silcock served as the Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President at Swift & Company since November 6, 2006 to 2007. Prior to that, he served as the Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President at Cott Corporation from 1998 to April 29, 2005 and Cott Beverages Inc. since September 1998, where he was responsible for driving the restructuring and turnaround of the business and also served as a Director of the firm. Prior to that, Mr. Silcock served as the Chief Financial Officer at Delimex Holdings Inc. from 1997 to 1998. Prior to that, he served as the Vice President of Finance and Chief Financial Officer for the Bakery and Confectionery Division at Campbell Soup Company until 1997, where he joined the firm in 1979 and spent 18 years at the firm in various financial management roles. Previously, Mr. Silcock also provided consulting services to Blackstone and Morgan Stanley since 2005. Currently, he also serves as an Independent Director of Pinnacle Foods Inc. and Pinnacle Foods Finance LLC since May 13, 2008. Previously, Mr. Silcock served as a Director of Bacardi Limited and Prestige Brands Holdings, Inc. from January 2006 to August 2009; and an Independent Director at American Italian Pasta Company, Inc. from July 18, 2006 to August 2, 2007. He has over 35 years of finance and accounting experience in the food and beverage industries. Mr. Silcock received an M.B.A. from the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania.Read Full Background




